705261f-c.title: Brooklyn: Kings Highway - Avenue J
705261f-c.text:
Kings Highway, north from Avenue J, showing
a W. P. A. highway project. The thoroughfare bends
eastward at Avenue 1 (white sign). Views 2 and 3 show
Kings Highway at Avenue I and East 45th Street, the row
of two-story dwellings being on the latter view 3 is
south from East 46th Street.
Views 1,2: Sept. 25, 193S
iews 3,4: Oct. 21, 1935
705261f-c.folder: Kings Highway & Avenue J, Brooklyn, NY

705254f-b.title: Brooklyn: Kings Highway - 45th Street (East)
705254f-b.text:
w1)  Kings Highway, east side,(on line of Ave. I,)between East 45th to
46th Streets, showing the Old Woolsey House, taked down in 1925. This
house was owned by Peter Hughes in 1857 and by Mrs Hughes in 1873.
1922.
Eugene L. Armbraster Collection.
MAY BE REPRODUCED.
(2)
The same, from another angle.
August 1924.
Eugene L. Armbruster Collection.
MAY BE REPRODUCED.
(3)
The same, showing the farmhouse occupied by William Garrett from
1860-1873.
April 1926.
Eugene L. Armbruster Collection.
MAY BE REPRODUCED.

705260f-a.title: Brooklyn: Kings Highway - Avenue J
705260f-a.text:
Eing's Highway, at the S.W. corner of Ave. J., shewing the Mayflaver
Hospital. Also seen is 4006-4012 Ave. J., south side, west from Eing's
Highway.
August 7, 1931.
P. L. Sperr.
